-- Unibail-Rodamco sells $1.1 bln mall portfolio to Wereldhave
-- By James Regan
-- Thu Oct 16, 2014 02:34AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, Oct 16 (Reuters) - Unibail-Rodamco <UNBP.AS> said it has agreed to sell a portfolio of six "non-core" French shopping centres for 850 million euros ($1.09 billion) to Wereldhave <WEHA.AS> as the French real estate group focuses on larger regional malls.

Wereldhave said it would finance the acquisition via a rights issue of up to 550 million euros, available cash of about 150 million and existing debt facilities. Completion of the transaction is expected by the end of December.